{
  "texts": [
    "Nay et al. (2023) used various models, noting that GPT-4 (the state of the art at the time) performed best and that they actually used GPT-4 to help grade their answers.",
    "Yu et al. (2022) used GPT-3.",
    "The most common area of law on which prior research focused is tax law.",
    "Nay et al. (2023), Blair-Stanek et al. (2023), and Choi et al. (2023) all included tax law in their studies.",
    "Bommarito II and Katz (2022) note that GPT-3.5 passed the evidence and torts section of the bar exam, and Choi et al. (2023) also included an examination paper on torts in their work."
  ]
}